response.overview: KRON-TV news footage from July 7th 1969 with reporter Mike Mills featuring scenes from an anti-fascist demonstration outside the Alameda County Administration Building in Oakland, at 1221 Oak Street, by groups including the Peace and Freedom Party and the Black Panther Party. Includes views of Black Panthers marching and singing, of Bobby Seale speaking and an interview with a man who describes a meeting they just had with the District Attorney. Opening graphic designed by Carrie Hawks.
response.title: Anti Fascist Demonstration in Oakland
